<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F38FF8C0700EF882" bold="true" box="[136,256,1854,1876]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D16FE5FBD11F20FF8C070C0F885" authorityName="Ferisin, Justo &amp; Dovana" authorityYear="2022" box="[264,462,1854,1876]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pluteaceae" genus="Pluteus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="4" pageNumber="153" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="aesontiensis">
<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F20FF8C070C0F885" box="[264,462,1854,1876]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Pluteus aesontiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(holotype). Micromorphological features. 
<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F075F8C07270F882" bold="true" box="[882,894,1854,1875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">a</emphasis>
Pileipellis. 
<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F0F2F8C0750CF882" bold="true" box="[1013,1026,1854,1875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">b</emphasis>
Spores. 
<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F75DF8C0756BF882" bold="true" box="[1114,1125,1854,1875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">c</emphasis>
Cheilocystidia. 
<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F601F8C0741DF882" bold="true" box="[1286,1299,1854,1875]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">d</emphasis>
Pleurocystidia. Bars:10 μm. Photos by G. Ferisin.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA03695FE5FBD11F3BAF85872FAF835" blockId="4.[136,1452,1958,2057]" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B96BEA87FE5FBD11F3BAF8587317F811" box="[189,537,1958,1984]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Habit, habitat and distribution</emphasis>
:—In groups, on broadleaved trees (trees present in the area: ashes, black-locust, elm, poplar and willow trees). So far, it is known only from northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3087605FE5FBD11F0BCF83472FEF835" box="[955,1008,1994,2020]" name="Italy" pageId="4" pageNumber="153">Italy</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
